survey_response.review_text: She is very amicable. Listens to the issues carefully and gives mental support along with proper diagnosis and medication.

I consulted with Dr. Rituparna Roy for severe Post COVID weakness/symptoms along with the long term issue of Chronic Fatigue Syndrome (CFS). Dr Roy is well aware of Post COVID issues and treatment as well as one of the rare doctors who is also aware of CFS. I also received a few home visits by Dr. Shrikant Mishra for face to face patient evaluation and also for getting saline IV drip at home. Dr. Mishra is very competent and has a jovial, engaging personality and a great bedside manner. I am very satisfied with both doctors who are polite, patient and attentive and certainly do recommend them.

I'm aged 72, suffered from fever with Cough and cold in 1stweek of Oct, took home remedies with antibiotics, but couldn't overcome it, lucky to have consulted Dr Rituparna Roy,a very knowledgeable doctor, very different than the current breed of consultants,as she relies on her diagnostic ability, physical examination,so doesn't overtest,overdrug you,got admitted in her boutique docville nursing home, within a week was up on feet ,ably supported by her 2ndin command Dr Shrikant, with a bill which would have costed me in a day at Ambani hospital! I wish more people come to consult her at Kulkarni hospital yamuna nagar Lokhandwala complex Andheri West, and get benefitted!

We went to Dr Roy, for consultation of my Mother Mrs Bhupinder Bhalla age 81yrs ECG report.
as her report says Sinus arrhythmia, rest all ok.
She compared her previous ECG report & she figured out May she wasn’t breathing properly while undergoing the ECG test & her observation were bang on , The next ECG undertaken on her advice ,was perfect without any variation. 
Thankyou Doc, really impressed by your calm, relax composure & friendly attitude & keen listener. 
God bless you. 🙏🏼🙏🏼
